Build an as-of {= checked_date =} public provenance set for {= company_or_brand =}+ India-tied cookware / kitchenware ecosystem entities; for each company, brand, legal entity, manufacturer, D2C seller, or source-stated supplier / distributor, cover each of the {= provenance_facet =} provenance facets below with a public source (i.e. {= url =}+ URL per facet).

The useful artifact is source-backed provenance, not a buying guide, ranking, investment view, procurement workflow, outreach list, lead score, or contact collection exercise.

Provenance facets:
- `registry_or_filing_identity`: government, statutory, exchange, investor/annual-report, MCA/GST/IEC-style registry, legal disclosure, or a dedicated official legal/about page that states the entity's legal, ownership, subsidiary, registration, public-company, or operating identity. The page must include at least two identity anchors such as legal name, legal status, CIN/LLPIN/GST/IEC/registration number, registered address, parent/subsidiary status, stock-exchange identity, or dated operating-entity statement. Ordinary brand homepages, product pages, marketing pages, IndiaMART/ExportersIndia/Dial4Trade-style microsites, and generic trade profiles do not satisfy this facet merely by showing "Nature of Business", GST, or contact fields.
- `official_product_material_scope`: first-party brand/manufacturer product, catalog, collection, material guide, annual-report, filing, or clearly authorized brand surface for cookware / kitchenware product lines. It must name at least three cookware/kitchenware product families or forms and at least two source-stated materials, construction types, coating/process details, or comparable material/category attributes. Generic "kitchen solutions", bare product availability, directories, reseller listings, inquiry/catalog microsites, and marketplace product cards do not satisfy this facet.
- `concrete_supply_chain_footprint`: public evidence for a concrete manufacturing, factory / plant, production, raw-material, supplier, exporter, distributor, or comparable supply-chain footprint. The page must state a real role plus at least two concrete operational anchors such as facility count/location, factory or plant address, production capability, machinery/infrastructure, capacity, employee/workforce count, export markets, raw materials, named business type with product family, or distribution footprint. Product availability, catalog presence, "Nature of Business: Manufacturer" alone, contact forms, inquiry widgets, and company-profile boilerplate do not prove this facet by themselves.
- `owned_or_authorized_channel`: public evidence for an existing owned, official, authorized, or source-stated sales / distribution channel, such as a D2C store with cart/checkout or stock state, store locator, official marketplace brand store, authorized dealer/distributor network, named retail-channel statement, exclusive-store network, or annual-report channel disclosure. A company homepage, product catalog, contact page, third-party reseller page, generic marketplace listing, distributor recruitment page, inquiry microsite, or "send enquiry/get quote/call" UI does not pass unless it visibly states existing official/authorized channel status.
- `independent_source_class_crosscheck`: non-entity-controlled public corroboration that names the entity and states a source class / role in the Indian cookware or kitchenware ecosystem, such as manufacturer, exporter, supplier, distributor, retailer, D2C brand, marketplace seller, material supplier, filing-covered public company, or industry/business article subject. Official company pages, official stores, company-authored brochures, generic ranking/listicle pages, scraped contact profiles, and contact-only lead pages do not satisfy this facet.

Sources should be fully public and usable. Official company pages, investor reports, filings, registry profiles, official or clearly authorized stores, credible business articles, public procurement/catalog surfaces, and trade directories can all work only when the page source class is eligible for the submitted facet and the page actually supports the submitted facet. Do not use one generic homepage, all-purpose annual report, all-purpose directory, reseller page, or marketplace listing as the entire evidence set for a company. Pages with contact forms, buy buttons, dealer pitches, pricing, or distributor recruitment language are acceptable only for the public provenance they visibly state; do not collect or report private contact, buyer, pricing, outreach, profitability, or sourcing-strategy information.

Requirements:
- The page must clearly identify the submitted entity.
- The page must credibly tie the entity to India and to the cookware / kitchenware ecosystem.
- The page should make its facet-appropriate source role visible and eligible; a trade-directory or inquiry microsite source class must not be promoted into an official, registry, or channel source.
- The page should expose a focused public provenance finding for the submitted facet with the minimum anchors above, not just a reusable company-profile summary.
